arts.ttl: The lowdown on Bromley 1 Tranmere 2 - Ravens lack real conviction after missing chance to end wait for League Two win
arts.sum: The best chance came on the half-hour mark when Imray crossed low for Olufela Olomola, who hit his effort high over the bar after being set up just in front of McGee’s goal. Bromley: Smith, Imray, Reynolds, Sowunmi, Grant, Odutayo, Charles [Leigh 45], Thompson [Congreve 76], Whitley, Olomola [Amantchi 45], Cheek [Dennis 55].

arts.ttl: ‘We’re relying on one man at the moment’ - Andy Woodman makes Bromley admission after Tranmere defeat
arts.sum: Andy Woodman says his Bromley squad are far too reliant on Michael Cheek after their 2-1 defeat at home to Tranmere on Saturday. Cheek has netted six times this season but was forced off in the 55th minute through injury.

arts.ttl: ‘They must have thought it was Christmas’ - Bromley boss left disappointed with defending in Tranmere defeat
arts.sum: “We had enough chances to put the game to bed at half-time. Andy Woodman said his Bromley side gifted Tranmere all three points in their 2-1 defeat at home on Saturday afternoon.

arts.ttl: Bromley boss asked for early Michael Cheek injury update after Tranmere defeat
arts.sum: Louis Dennis pulled one back in the final minutes of stoppage time. Bromley boss Andy Woodman says Michael Cheek was withdrawn as a precaution during their 2-1 defeat to Tranmere on Saturday.

arts.ttl: Tranmere end winless run with late victory at Bromley
Bromley attacker believes late professional start will extend playing career
arts.sum: Corey Whitely believes his late start in professional football will allow him to extend his playing career with Bromley. Whitely has gone on to record close to 300 National League appearances during spells with Bromley, Ebbsfleet and Dagenham & Redbridge.

arts.ttl: Free agent snapped up by new club after Tranmere Rovers exit
